description:
&lt;p&gt;The Community Therapy Service provides patient centred rehabilitation for patients in the community and Short Stay beds within Oxfordshire. If you would like the opportunity to assess and provide high quality, patient centred rehabilitation and support within a patients own home environment/ digitally, then come and work with us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are inviting applications from enthusiastic and innovative Band 6 or experienced band 5 Occupational Therapists to work with us. You will be working as part of a team of Physiotherapists, Occupational Therapists, Mental Health Practitioners, Assistant Practitioners and Rehabilitation Assistants providing short term rehabilitation to enable patients to lead as independent a life as possible. You will be working closely with specialist nurses and wider MDT including NHS and other community providers to provide holistic patient centred care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Community Therapy is at the forefront of current government initiatives to deliver more healthcare out of acute hospitals and closer to home with the aim of providing better care for patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key elements of the post include managing a varied case load and assisting with service development and improvement. Flexible working is required for provision of service over seven days and extended hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent education and training opportunities are available to the team members. Ongoing staff support within the Appraisal and Supervision guidelines are provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Own car or access to alternative travel for business use is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is predominantly based in the South East locality, in Wallingford hospital. There are some short stay beds within this locality that you may be expected to work from.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This vacancy will close as soon as sufficient applications have been received. Please apply early if interested.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lisa Bracher (joint clinical lead OT) T: 0746 449 4104, email lisa.bracher@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk or Penny McCrabbe (joint clinical lead PT) T: 07887831393, email Penelope.clayton@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
